    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-07-05T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-07-05T05:00:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340/7–553: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation to the
                            Economic and Social Council</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department
                            of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-07-05T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 5, 1953—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">Ecosoc</gloss> 12. In light <gloss
                        target="#t_ECOSOC1">Ecosoc</gloss> 4 and supplement<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d447fn1">Neither printed.</note> likely Chinese representation issue
                    raised on report credentials. In unlikely case issue raised inform 1(B) Socec 1
                        <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> intends handle issue in accordance
                        <pb facs="0712" n="684" xml:id="pg_684"/> position paper moving adjournment
                    debate for duration sixteenth session stating effect would not only be (<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>) continued seating of Chinese Nationalist
                    representatives but also (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) rejection request for
                    inclusion item on agenda. <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> agrees.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ALLENWP1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
